WEBVTT

00:00:09.687 --> 00:00:19.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who is your friend, O God?
Who in your tent may dwell?

00:00:19.479 --> 00:00:24.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who gains your friendship?
Who gains your trust?

00:00:24.229 --> 00:00:33.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who really knows you well?
All who embrace your Word,

00:00:33.979 --> 00:00:43.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All who have faith in you,
All who are loyal, all who are just,

00:00:43.604 --> 00:00:48.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Living the truth for you.

00:00:55.729 --> 00:01:05.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who is your friend, O God?
Who may approach your throne?

00:01:05.604 --> 00:01:15.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who brings delight and Makes you rejoice?
Whose name to you is known?

00:01:15.104 --> 00:01:24.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All who exalt your name,
All who your Word obey,

00:01:24.812 --> 00:01:34.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All who are faithful, honest in heart,
Truthful in all they say.

00:01:36.979 --> 00:01:46.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Rolling our cares on you,
Baring our hearts in prayer,

00:01:46.645 --> 00:01:56.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Drawing us closer, bonding in love,
Feeling your daily care,

00:01:56.395 --> 00:02:06.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We yearn to be your friend.
Long may our friendship grow.

00:02:06.062 --> 00:02:15.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No greater Friend could we ever gain,
No greater Friend we’ll know.

00:02:15.645 --> 00:02:28.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No greater Friend could we ever gain,
No greater Friend we’ll know.

